WEBVTT

00:02.919 --> 00:05.797
[rock music]

00:05.880 --> 00:08.299
(kids)
Pig!

00:09.426 --> 00:12.345
Goat!

00:13.555 --> 00:14.848
Banana!

00:14.931 --> 00:19.519
♪ ♪

00:19.602 --> 00:20.770
Cricket!

00:20.854 --> 00:28.153
♪ ♪

00:33.533 --> 00:35.160
A-a-a-achoo!

00:35.243 --> 00:38.413
(all)
Pig! Goat! Banana! Cricket!

00:41.750 --> 00:44.753
[mysterious music]

00:44.836 --> 00:50.717
♪ ♪

00:50.800 --> 00:53.762
[electronic music]

00:53.845 --> 01:01.853
♪ ♪

01:09.068 --> 01:10.028
[all cheering]

01:10.111 --> 01:11.154
[stork squawks]

01:13.531 --> 01:17.786
{\an5}(all)
Pig Goat Banana Cricket
Power picnic high five!

01:17.869 --> 01:21.748
Oh, wouldn't it be great if
bubbles were made out of fudge?

01:21.831 --> 01:24.042
Or even better...

01:24.125 --> 01:25.752
Pickle milk?

01:25.835 --> 01:27.962
[country music]

01:28.046 --> 01:29.339
Pickle milk?

01:29.422 --> 01:30.673
That's the most disgusting--

01:30.757 --> 01:32.008
{\an3}[gagging]

01:32.091 --> 01:33.092
{\an3}Hey!

01:33.176 --> 01:34.761
Hey, you got to be faster

01:34.844 --> 01:37.931
{\an1}if you're going to catch
Fantasy Pig.

01:38.014 --> 01:39.682
{\an1}Goat, was that legit
when you said

01:39.766 --> 01:41.226
{\an1}you wish there were
fudge bubbles?

01:41.309 --> 01:42.477
{\an3}Of course.

01:42.560 --> 01:44.854
Think how much better
everything would be.

01:44.938 --> 01:47.524
{\an3}It would solve
all the world's problems.

01:47.607 --> 01:52.779
If you want a fudge bubble,
I'll make you a fudge bubble.

01:52.862 --> 01:53.696
{\an3}What?

01:53.780 --> 01:55.198
{\an1}What?
Oh, good talk.

01:55.281 --> 01:56.241
Got to go. Bye.

01:56.324 --> 01:59.369
Oh, man.
Who ate all the potato salad?

01:59.452 --> 02:00.703
[country music]
- [chuckles]

02:00.787 --> 02:01.871
I did.

02:01.955 --> 02:03.873
Fantasy Pig.

02:03.957 --> 02:08.044
- Ah!
- [gurgling]

02:08.127 --> 02:09.169
{\an3}Yum.

02:09.253 --> 02:09.838
{\an1}[gagging]

02:09.920 --> 02:13.716
[machine beeping]

02:17.470 --> 02:18.888
Hi, Cricket, what ya doing?

02:18.972 --> 02:20.598
{\an3}[shouts]
Oh, hi, Pig.

02:20.682 --> 02:23.726
{\an3}How did you get past
my laser security system?

02:23.810 --> 02:25.728
Just lucky, I guess.

02:25.812 --> 02:28.690
I smell bacon. Yum.

02:28.773 --> 02:30.900
{\an3}I'm working on a top secret
project for Goat

02:30.984 --> 02:33.278
{\an3}that absolutely no one
can know about.

02:33.361 --> 02:34.028
{\an3}No one.

02:34.112 --> 02:36.322
Oh, you can help me test it.

02:36.406 --> 02:38.533
[machine beeps]

02:38.616 --> 02:39.617
[yells]

02:40.660 --> 02:43.746
Presenting the Fudge Bubbler!

02:43.830 --> 02:46.875
[dramatic music]

02:48.084 --> 02:50.378
[bubbling]

02:53.506 --> 02:54.799
Open wide, Pig.

02:54.883 --> 02:59.095
{\an1}Can't. I'm doing a, uh,
lasagna cleanse.

02:59.178 --> 03:00.346
Doctor's orders.

03:00.430 --> 03:03.141
[grunting]

03:03.224 --> 03:04.100
Hmm?

03:04.183 --> 03:06.102
[gagging]

03:06.185 --> 03:07.645
[magical chiming]

03:07.729 --> 03:08.605
[gasps]

03:08.688 --> 03:12.609
Whoa!

03:16.154 --> 03:17.155
{\an1}Okay.

03:17.238 --> 03:19.991
{\an1}That was only the most
amazing thing

03:20.074 --> 03:22.702
I have ever had in my life.

03:22.785 --> 03:23.995
Can I have another?

03:24.078 --> 03:25.538
Sorry, they're for Goat.

03:25.622 --> 03:29.626
And don't touch my machine.
It's not a toy.

03:29.709 --> 03:30.627
Hi, Cricket.

03:30.710 --> 03:32.295
Oh, h-hey, Goat.

03:32.378 --> 03:33.421
What are you doing?

03:33.504 --> 03:34.839
Oh, I'm glad you asked

03:34.923 --> 03:36.090
{\an3}because I made
something for you

03:36.174 --> 03:37.842
that's so incredible, so--

03:37.926 --> 03:41.930
{\an1}It's the most butt-rageous thing
I've eaten in my entire life.

03:42.013 --> 03:42.972
[clears throat]

03:43.056 --> 03:44.974
It's The Fudge Bubbler.

03:45.058 --> 03:46.184
What'd you invent for me?

03:46.267 --> 03:46.768
{\an1}Nothing.

03:46.851 --> 03:49.854
Ah, I get it.

03:49.938 --> 03:50.980
A surprise.

03:51.064 --> 03:52.815
[sipping]

03:52.899 --> 03:55.234
{\an3}Remember when you said
you wanted a fudge bubble?

03:55.318 --> 03:58.112
{\an1}What? I never said that
in my entire life.

03:58.196 --> 03:59.238
You totally said it.

03:59.322 --> 04:01.074
{\an3}Come on.
Think.

04:01.157 --> 04:04.786
Aw. Let's go to the video tape.

04:04.869 --> 04:07.497
{\an3}Wait a second, you film
all our picnics?

04:07.580 --> 04:09.874
Not all of them.

04:09.958 --> 04:13.920
Wouldn't it be great if bubbles
were made out of fudge?

04:14.003 --> 04:16.172
No, I don't remember this.

04:16.255 --> 04:18.007
Zoom and enhance.

04:18.091 --> 04:23.012
{\an5}(in slow motion)
Wouldn't it be great if
bubbles were made out of fudge?

04:23.096 --> 04:24.722
Nuh-uh, not ringing a bell.

04:24.806 --> 04:26.432
Zoom and enhance.

04:26.516 --> 04:29.852
(in deeper voice)
Wouldn't it be great--

04:29.936 --> 04:30.853
No, total blank.

04:30.937 --> 04:35.733
But I look great.

04:35.817 --> 04:36.859
[panting]

04:36.943 --> 04:39.612
For you, Goat.

04:39.696 --> 04:41.364
What am I supposed to do
with it?

04:41.447 --> 04:44.701
- You eat it.
- Okay. Here I go.

04:44.784 --> 04:45.827
[splashing]
- [mumbling]

04:45.910 --> 04:48.162
{\an1}[slurping]

04:48.246 --> 04:51.207
[bell dings]
- [grunts]

04:51.290 --> 04:53.126
Totally worth it.

04:53.209 --> 04:55.378
Um, I'm gonna take a shower.

04:55.461 --> 04:57.130
No, wait.
I can--

04:57.213 --> 04:58.381
[sighs]

04:58.464 --> 04:59.382
That's it.

04:59.465 --> 05:00.550
Come on, everybody out.

05:00.633 --> 05:02.176
G-g-g-g-go.
No more fudge bubbles.

05:02.260 --> 05:03.594
- Go, go.
- But I didn't even get one--

05:03.678 --> 05:05.138
{\an3}[shouts]

05:05.221 --> 05:05.471
{\an1}Wheee!

05:07.640 --> 05:08.933
When you said "no,"

05:09.017 --> 05:10.393
did you mean "no' or--

05:10.476 --> 05:12.437
{\an1}[shouts]

05:15.815 --> 05:17.150
[sleep talking]

05:17.233 --> 05:20.069
Fudge Bubbles.
Fudge Bubbles.

05:20.153 --> 05:21.237
Got to have fudge bubbles.

05:21.320 --> 05:22.697
[gasps]
Fudge bubbles!

05:22.780 --> 05:25.742
[exciting music]

05:25.825 --> 05:28.077
♪ ♪

05:30.538 --> 05:33.082
Got to be careful.

05:33.166 --> 05:35.960
[kiaiing]

05:36.044 --> 05:38.171
[gong chimes]

05:38.254 --> 05:39.172
[panting]

05:39.255 --> 05:42.133
[lasers beeping]

05:42.216 --> 05:42.884
[laser beam whizzes]

05:42.967 --> 05:45.928
[screaming]

05:46.012 --> 05:47.597
[sniffing]

05:47.680 --> 05:48.973
I smell bacon again.

05:49.057 --> 05:49.932
Yum.

05:50.016 --> 05:53.061
[buzz saws whirring]

05:54.937 --> 05:56.397
Tear gas?

05:56.481 --> 05:57.774
Yum.

05:57.857 --> 05:59.400
[robotic dogs barking]

05:59.484 --> 06:01.110
Cybernetic dogs?

06:01.194 --> 06:04.113
Yummy, yum, yum.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.490
[burping]

06:05.573 --> 06:07.784
[playful music]

06:07.867 --> 06:10.578
♪ ♪

06:12.789 --> 06:14.248
Hmm.

06:14.332 --> 06:16.793
What was it Cricket said
about the Fudge Bubbler thingy?

06:16.876 --> 06:19.253
{\an3}Touch my machine.
It's a toy.

06:19.337 --> 06:20.838
Okay, if you say so.

06:20.922 --> 06:23.007
[buttons beeping]
- Yippee!

06:23.091 --> 06:26.719
[machine whirring]

06:26.803 --> 06:29.222
What's with all the brouhaha?

06:29.305 --> 06:30.515
{\an3}Hey, guys.

06:30.598 --> 06:33.142
Oh, it's only those nasty
fudge balls.

06:33.226 --> 06:33.893
{\an3}Nasty?

06:33.976 --> 06:35.978
{\an3}You nasty!

06:36.062 --> 06:36.854
They're amazing.

06:36.938 --> 06:38.523
{\an3}Try one.

06:38.606 --> 06:40.775
[magical chiming]

06:40.858 --> 06:43.444
That was the most butt-rageous
thing I've ever eaten

06:43.528 --> 06:45.029
in my entire life.

06:45.113 --> 06:47.240
I know right?

06:47.323 --> 06:49.158
Fudge Bubble party.

06:49.242 --> 06:50.159
[bubbling]

06:50.243 --> 06:51.119
[upbeat music]

06:51.202 --> 06:54.205
[all laughing and cheering]

06:54.288 --> 07:00.378
♪ ♪

07:00.461 --> 07:01.796
{\an3}Pop. Whoo!

07:01.879 --> 07:02.421
[laughs]

07:02.505 --> 07:03.089
- Whoo.
- Oh.

07:03.172 --> 07:05.174
I got it, I got it.

07:05.258 --> 07:06.050
It's bouncing, it's bouncing--

07:06.134 --> 07:08.761
Here I go, here I go.

07:08.845 --> 07:10.429
Touchdown.

07:10.513 --> 07:11.889
[laughter]

07:11.973 --> 07:13.975
Fudge Bubbles.

07:14.058 --> 07:17.103
[all shouting]

07:19.105 --> 07:20.022
[gasps]

07:20.106 --> 07:21.858
[mumbling]

07:21.941 --> 07:23.192
[gasps]

07:27.155 --> 07:28.281
The Fudge Bubbler.

07:28.364 --> 07:30.700
It's totally out of control.

07:30.783 --> 07:33.369
Pig, I told you not to touch it!

07:33.452 --> 07:35.204
{\an1}Oh, not.

07:35.288 --> 07:36.205
Whoopsy dingles.

07:36.289 --> 07:36.873
{\an3}[shouting]

07:36.956 --> 07:37.874
{\an1}[gasps]

07:37.957 --> 07:39.542
{\an1}Cricket!

07:39.625 --> 07:41.878
[suspenseful music]

07:41.961 --> 07:50.720
♪ ♪

07:51.929 --> 07:53.723
{\an1}Cricket!
I'll fix it!

07:53.806 --> 07:55.308
I'll fix everything!

07:55.391 --> 07:56.934
[screams]

07:57.018 --> 07:57.894
Cricket!

07:57.977 --> 07:59.312
[screams]

07:59.395 --> 08:01.689
[dramatic music]

08:03.441 --> 08:04.275
[gasps]

08:04.358 --> 08:05.902
Don't worry, Cricket.

08:05.985 --> 08:08.529
[grunts]

08:08.613 --> 08:10.573
[crowd murmuring]

08:10.656 --> 08:12.909
- [shouting]
- [grunting]

08:12.992 --> 08:16.704
♪ ♪

08:16.787 --> 08:19.123
(Cricket)
Help me, Pig.

08:19.207 --> 08:22.168
[both shouting]

08:22.251 --> 08:23.252
♪ ♪

08:23.336 --> 08:23.628
Whoa!

08:26.964 --> 08:28.257
Cricket!

08:28.341 --> 08:30.343
[sobbing]

08:34.597 --> 08:36.097
I gotta save Cricket.

08:36.182 --> 08:38.517
But first,
how do I get off this bubble?

08:38.601 --> 08:41.729
[helicopters whirring]
- Uh-oh.

08:42.855 --> 08:44.232
{\an8}Chet, it looks like
the mega-bubble

08:44.315 --> 08:45.733
{\an8}is starting to drip.

08:45.816 --> 08:47.443
{\an8}At any moment it could burst,
drowning the world in--

08:47.526 --> 08:49.946
{\an9}Umbrellas!
I got umbrellas here!

08:50.029 --> 08:51.113
{\an9}Keep your heads
fudge-free

08:51.197 --> 08:52.281
{\an9}with these official
Fudge-pocalypse umbrell--

08:52.365 --> 08:54.784
{\an8}Ugh--Hey, get your hands off me.

08:54.867 --> 08:57.203
{\an7}At any moment it could
burst, drowning the world in--

08:57.286 --> 08:59.789
{\an8}Fudge proof underpants.

08:59.872 --> 09:02.458
{\an9}His and Hers
while supplies last.

09:02.541 --> 09:05.419
[weeping]

09:05.503 --> 09:07.129
I gotta save Cricket.

09:07.213 --> 09:10.299
How am I ever gonna
get off of this bubble?

09:10.383 --> 09:10.716
[stork squawks]

09:13.052 --> 09:15.888
Great idea.

09:15.972 --> 09:17.723
[Fudge Bubble explodes]

09:17.807 --> 09:19.058
[screaming]

09:19.141 --> 09:20.935
{\an3}[squawks]

09:21.602 --> 09:23.104
Follow that cricket.

09:27.233 --> 09:28.693
[rumbling]

09:28.776 --> 09:31.362
[loud splashing]

09:31.445 --> 09:33.489
It's the Fudge-pocalypse.

09:33.572 --> 09:34.824
Help, mon!

09:37.410 --> 09:38.828
We're all doomed.

09:38.911 --> 09:42.540
{\an3}I've been planning for this day
my entire life.

09:42.623 --> 09:44.542
{\an1}You've been planning for a
Fudgepocalypse your whole life?

09:44.625 --> 09:47.920
{\an3}What?
No, I'm not a lunatic.

09:48.004 --> 09:50.089
{\an3}I also planned
for the Peppermintpocalypse,

09:50.172 --> 09:53.175
{\an3}Caramel-pocalypse, and the
Mint Chocolate Chip-pocalypse.

09:53.259 --> 09:56.637
[dramatic music]

09:56.721 --> 09:58.848
<i>Et voilà!</i>

09:58.931 --> 09:59.932
[tree cranking open]

10:00.016 --> 10:01.934
♪ ♪

10:02.018 --> 10:02.560
A giant boat.

10:02.643 --> 10:04.645
We're all saved!

10:04.729 --> 10:08.816
♪ ♪

10:08.899 --> 10:10.276
Come with me
if you want to live.

10:10.359 --> 10:13.446
[all shouting at once]
- Go, go, go!

10:13.529 --> 10:20.578
♪ ♪

10:20.661 --> 10:22.371
Excuse me. Hello?

10:22.455 --> 10:25.791
If we can all just quiet down
for a second--

10:25.875 --> 10:26.834
[bullhorn giving feedback]

10:26.917 --> 10:31.213
Hi.
Welcome to my boat.

10:31.297 --> 10:33.007
I'm super glad you're all here.

10:33.090 --> 10:35.217
{\an3}I think.

10:35.301 --> 10:37.219
{\an1}Thanks for making room
for Sleazy Beave, Gorgeous.

10:37.303 --> 10:39.180
{\an1}[sniffing]

10:39.263 --> 10:42.725
You're the audience
I've always wanted.

10:42.808 --> 10:43.976
Let's start with a sing-a-long.

10:44.060 --> 10:50.274
♪ Row, row, row, your boat,
gently down the fudge ♪

10:50.358 --> 10:52.943
♪ Merrily, merrily,
merrily, merrily ♪

10:53.027 --> 10:55.363
♪ Life is pretty much over
as we know it ♪

10:55.446 --> 10:56.739
{\an3}Goat,
what's the Wi-Fi password?

10:56.822 --> 10:58.491
We don't have Wi-Fi.

10:58.574 --> 10:59.658
No Wi-Fi?

10:59.742 --> 11:01.118
Then how am I supposed
to download

11:01.202 --> 11:02.661
"Midnight Passion Possums"?

11:02.745 --> 11:04.872
[all murmuring]
Midnight Passion Possums?

11:04.955 --> 11:07.291
{\an1}All right, all right, all right,
all right, all right.

11:07.375 --> 11:09.001
{\an1}I'll build a satellite.
It'll be tough but--

11:09.085 --> 11:11.712
{\an3}Less talk-y,
more satellite build-y.

11:11.796 --> 11:14.340
{\an1}You bone blang flung flibbet
satellite shazbot!

11:14.423 --> 11:17.468
{\an3}Hey! I must be going crazy,
cause that looks like Cricket.

11:17.551 --> 11:19.887
I'm in a fudge bubble.
Get me out of here.

11:19.970 --> 11:21.430
{\an1}[gasps]
It is Cricket.

11:21.514 --> 11:22.431
Hey, Cricket.
How ya doing?

11:22.515 --> 11:24.392
Get me out of here.

11:24.475 --> 11:25.434
What's he saying?

11:25.518 --> 11:26.894
{\an1}Hang on.
I read lips.

11:26.977 --> 11:27.895
- Goat.
- He says--

11:27.978 --> 11:29.605
- Help!
- I'm fine.

11:29.688 --> 11:32.108
- Banana!
- We're fine, too.

11:32.191 --> 11:34.902
- We love you.
- I'm in the bubble...

11:34.985 --> 11:36.278
He looks great.

11:36.362 --> 11:37.279
Yeah, nice guy.

11:37.363 --> 11:38.697
{\an3}Did you finish
the satellite yet?

11:38.781 --> 11:39.907
I'm gonna satellite your neck.

11:41.951 --> 11:44.245
{\an1}Please, I need
something to eat.

11:44.328 --> 11:45.246
[upbeat music]

11:45.329 --> 11:46.414
Well, how about some fillet
of fudge

11:46.497 --> 11:48.791
in a Tuscan fudge sauce

11:48.874 --> 11:51.710
with Fudgeghetti
and Icelandic fudge wedges?

11:51.794 --> 11:54.046
{\an1}I ain't eating any more fudge,
lady!

11:54.130 --> 11:57.341
Um, Beave, what's your grudge
against fudge?

11:57.425 --> 11:59.927
{\an1}We've had it up to ya-ya
with fudge.

12:00.010 --> 12:02.096
We are fudged out over here.

12:02.179 --> 12:04.807
Yeah, when are we going to get
some real food up here?

12:04.890 --> 12:07.726
{\an1}Has anyone ever told you
that you look like a banana?

12:07.810 --> 12:10.312
- Mmm.
- Yeah, I get that all the time.

12:10.396 --> 12:13.149
Uh, actually, no.

12:13.232 --> 12:14.275
{\an3}No. I don't get that.
Ever.

12:14.358 --> 12:15.234
Get him!

12:15.317 --> 12:17.987
[all shouting]

12:18.070 --> 12:19.447
Goat, you got to help me.

12:19.530 --> 12:20.823
I'll help, all right.

12:20.906 --> 12:21.907
{\an1}I'll help feed you
to those guys.

12:21.991 --> 12:24.869
{\an1}You have been so rude to me
this entire trip.

12:24.952 --> 12:26.412
No. Wait, wait, wait.

12:26.495 --> 12:28.122
I know I've been demanding
and ungrateful lately,

12:28.205 --> 12:30.583
but this Fudge-pocalypse
is really stressing me out.

12:30.666 --> 12:31.876
My umbrella business is tanking.

12:31.959 --> 12:35.671
Look, I'm sorry I treated
you like dirt.

12:35.754 --> 12:38.382
[crying]

12:38.466 --> 12:41.510
Weird rambling apology accepted.

12:41.594 --> 12:42.470
Back off!

12:42.553 --> 12:43.846
This is my friend!

12:43.929 --> 12:44.430
Ah! You hear that?

12:44.513 --> 12:46.390
I'm her friend.

12:46.474 --> 12:47.683
And I'm not afraid to use him.

12:47.766 --> 12:49.894
Yeah and she's not afraid--

12:49.977 --> 12:50.394
Wait, what?

12:50.478 --> 12:52.271
[shouting]

12:52.354 --> 12:53.272
I'm gonna banana
your brains out.

12:53.355 --> 12:55.483
[grunting]

12:55.566 --> 12:59.403
[all shouting at once]

13:00.613 --> 13:02.156
{\an1}Banana, find us a way out
of here.

13:02.239 --> 13:04.408
Right. I'm on it.

13:04.492 --> 13:05.784
[all shouting]

13:05.868 --> 13:06.827
Not in there.

13:06.911 --> 13:09.038
The porthole.

13:09.121 --> 13:12.166
[shouting nonsense]

13:13.751 --> 13:16.670
Don't worry.
I got this.

13:16.754 --> 13:19.006
[shouting]

13:22.510 --> 13:24.303
{\an3}So, uh, does this toilet
get Wi-Fi?

13:28.724 --> 13:31.477
[dramatic music]

13:31.560 --> 13:37.233
Faster, Mr. Bird,
we're losing Cricket.

13:37.316 --> 13:40.903
That's not helping, Mr. Bird.

13:40.986 --> 13:44.031
[screaming]

13:45.658 --> 13:47.910
- Whoa!
- Banana!

13:49.411 --> 13:50.829
[screaming]

13:50.913 --> 13:51.956
Fudge.

13:52.039 --> 13:53.290
[sputtering]

13:53.374 --> 13:56.835
Help! Help!
I don't feel like swimming!

13:56.919 --> 13:57.962
[choking]

13:59.380 --> 14:02.341
[magical shimmering]

14:02.424 --> 14:03.634
[burping]

14:03.717 --> 14:05.970
My lungs had a lot of fudge
in them.

14:06.053 --> 14:06.929
Oh, thanks.

14:07.012 --> 14:09.265
Thanks for saving my life.

14:09.348 --> 14:12.309
[growling]

14:12.393 --> 14:13.269
[gasps]

14:13.352 --> 14:14.270
[stuttering]

14:14.353 --> 14:17.398
[ominous music]

14:18.524 --> 14:21.110
Pirates.
We're pirates.

14:21.193 --> 14:23.195
No, no, I mean I--
[stuttering]

14:23.279 --> 14:24.780
peed my peel.

14:24.863 --> 14:26.699
Oh, really?

14:30.369 --> 14:31.787
Wait, wait wait!
No, no, no, no, no.

14:31.870 --> 14:34.832
Don't hurt me.
I'll do anything you want.

14:34.915 --> 14:36.292
Oh, jolly good, right.

14:36.375 --> 14:37.751
Swab the deck.

14:37.835 --> 14:41.714
That's not really my style.

14:41.797 --> 14:42.715
Not your style?

14:42.798 --> 14:44.800
{\an1}Maybe battening down
the hatches?

14:44.883 --> 14:46.260
[screaming]

14:46.343 --> 14:49.430
{\an3}Here's the thing.
No, I'm not a big battener.

14:49.513 --> 14:51.765
{\an1}Not a battener either.
Oh, that's too bad.

14:51.849 --> 14:54.560
{\an1}Alright, then.
Hoist the main sail.

14:54.643 --> 14:56.562
{\an3}Like how you said it:
"Hoist!"

14:56.645 --> 14:59.315
{\an3}But like battening,
hoisting's not really my thing.

14:59.398 --> 15:01.150
You guys have Wi-Fi?

15:01.233 --> 15:03.485
{\an3}Oh, and I don't do
swashbuckling.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.029
{\an1}Oh, right.

15:05.112 --> 15:08.657
{\an1}You'll be telling us what
ye <i> do</i> do little man.

15:08.741 --> 15:10.159
{\an3}[laughs]
You said "do-do."

15:10.242 --> 15:13.871
Or we'll walk you right off
the plank.

15:13.954 --> 15:14.955
{\an3}[roaring]

15:15.039 --> 15:16.749
Gulp.

15:16.832 --> 15:19.376
I'll sit in that thing.

15:19.460 --> 15:22.963
{\an1}N'yar, fine.
But no sleeping on the job.

15:23.047 --> 15:23.964
{\an3}[laughs]

15:24.048 --> 15:25.007
{\an1}What now?

15:25.090 --> 15:28.510
{\an3}You said "do-do."
Remember?

15:28.594 --> 15:32.222
Got it. Got it, no sleeping.
Aye-aye.

15:32.306 --> 15:35.351
[grunting]

15:36.894 --> 15:38.020
[laughs]

15:38.103 --> 15:39.521
Those pirate suckers.

15:39.605 --> 15:42.358
I can't believe they actually
call this a job.

15:42.441 --> 15:45.486
[yawning]

15:46.904 --> 15:47.905
Cozy.

15:47.988 --> 15:50.949
[chuckles]

15:51.033 --> 15:52.868
Stupid pirates.

15:52.951 --> 15:55.245
Banana! Get me out of here!

15:55.329 --> 15:57.247
Help! Banana! Banana!

15:57.331 --> 15:59.792
[loud thud]
- [screams]

15:59.875 --> 16:01.210
[all screaming]

16:01.293 --> 16:06.173
{\an3}You sank my ship, you scurvy
yellow scallywag.

16:06.256 --> 16:09.301
[dramatic music]

16:10.260 --> 16:11.470
[screaming]

16:11.553 --> 16:15.724
Paddle faster, Pig.
I sense Banana is near.

16:15.808 --> 16:18.560
[adventurous music]

16:18.644 --> 16:22.523
Keep walking, you foulmouthed,
sleeping scallywag.

16:22.606 --> 16:23.857
No, wait, wait, wait, wait.

16:23.941 --> 16:25.442
No, you can't send me
off the plank.

16:25.526 --> 16:27.152
And why not?

16:27.236 --> 16:28.654
No, because, uh, because--

16:28.737 --> 16:30.239
Yeah, that's it.
That's it.

16:30.322 --> 16:34.243
I can lead you parrot kissers
to buried treasure.

16:34.326 --> 16:38.038
And where be this buried
treasure ye speak of?

16:38.122 --> 16:39.581
We, uh--

16:39.665 --> 16:42.584
We just follow this wild goose.

16:42.668 --> 16:45.087
Hold on hornswaggler.

16:45.170 --> 16:48.590
Are ye sending us
on a wild goose chase?

16:48.674 --> 16:49.800
Uh...

16:49.883 --> 16:50.801
That's right.

16:50.884 --> 16:53.887
[suspenseful music]

16:53.971 --> 16:55.764
Proceed.

16:55.848 --> 16:57.266
I miss Cricket.

16:57.349 --> 16:58.976
And I miss Banana.

16:59.059 --> 17:01.395
[gasps]
Dry land!

17:01.478 --> 17:04.356
(Pig)
Yippee!

17:04.440 --> 17:05.648
We're saved!

17:05.733 --> 17:07.317
[kissing sound]
[headhunters murmuring]

17:07.401 --> 17:11.113
Hello. Would you like to take
a ride in my toilet boat?

17:11.195 --> 17:15.159
I'm thinking
that's a no, right?

17:15.242 --> 17:18.787
[both snoring]

17:21.457 --> 17:23.208
{\an3}Whoa!

17:23.291 --> 17:24.626
Ow. Ow. Ow.

17:24.710 --> 17:28.172
Ow.
Ooh, coconuts, yum!

17:28.255 --> 17:30.340
[screaming]

17:30.424 --> 17:31.592
(kids)
Cricket!

17:31.675 --> 17:33.510
Whoa-ho-ho-ho-ho.

17:33.594 --> 17:36.388
How do I get out
of here?

17:36.472 --> 17:38.932
Whoa-ho, yeoh!
[grunts]

17:39.016 --> 17:40.225
- [squawking]
- Whoo-hoo-hoo.

17:40.309 --> 17:42.895
Hello?
Anyone here?

17:42.978 --> 17:44.563
Hello?

17:44.646 --> 17:45.898
I'm alone.

17:45.981 --> 17:48.650
- Except for this bird.
- [squawking]

17:48.734 --> 17:50.986
Completely alone!

17:51.069 --> 17:52.321
I don't need friends.

17:52.404 --> 17:56.200
I don't need anybody!
[echoing]

17:56.283 --> 17:59.995
{\an1}I've completed my new home
in paradise.

18:00.078 --> 18:02.372
I don't have to share it
with anybody.

18:02.456 --> 18:03.707
Except for you, Goat.

18:03.791 --> 18:05.083
What do you think, Goat?

18:05.167 --> 18:06.835
(imitating Goat)
Ooh, I love it,

18:06.919 --> 18:09.254
and I love you even more.

18:09.338 --> 18:11.215
[kissing sounds]

18:11.298 --> 18:12.800
Ah, shucks, Goat.

18:12.883 --> 18:13.967
And you, Banana.

18:14.051 --> 18:15.552
{\an1}(imitating Banana)
I give you a hard time

18:15.636 --> 18:18.013
{\an1}only because I'm jealous
of how smart and great you are.

18:18.096 --> 18:20.432
{\an1}Oh, well, I know, buddy.
I know.

18:20.516 --> 18:23.060
(imitating Pig)
Pickles! That's my favorite!

18:23.143 --> 18:25.521
Oh, Pig, just like old times.

18:25.604 --> 18:27.105
[sobbing]

18:27.189 --> 18:29.358
I miss you all so much.

18:29.441 --> 18:33.695
I'm so lonely.
Ah!

18:33.779 --> 18:35.030
- Cricket!
- [gasps]

18:35.114 --> 18:36.740
Goat, you're alive!

18:36.824 --> 18:38.742
- Good times.
- What is that?

18:38.826 --> 18:41.703
Oh, that's just a life-sized
replica of you I built,

18:41.787 --> 18:43.205
then pretended
it would marry me.

18:43.288 --> 18:45.415
- What?
- What?

18:45.499 --> 18:47.125
So, where are we going?

18:47.209 --> 18:50.754
Into that volcano.

18:50.838 --> 18:51.880
Bad times.

18:51.964 --> 18:55.676
Me patience be wearing thin,
fruit man.

18:55.759 --> 18:56.927
Where's the treasure?

18:57.010 --> 19:00.264
- It's right--
- [roaring]

19:00.347 --> 19:01.348
{\an3}Oh, crud.

19:01.431 --> 19:03.392
There is no treasure.

19:03.475 --> 19:08.021
Ye be a fibber.

19:08.105 --> 19:11.984
Oh, no. Goat and Cricket
are tied up by headhunters.

19:12.067 --> 19:13.235
They'll save me!

19:13.318 --> 19:15.696
{\an3}There's the treasure.
That island.

19:15.779 --> 19:17.781
All right, uh, mateys.

19:17.865 --> 19:19.575
The treasures at that volcano.

19:19.658 --> 19:21.785
{\an3}Swivel the boom,
or whatever it is you do.

19:21.869 --> 19:23.328
Just get us there.

19:23.412 --> 19:25.914
[all shouting]

19:25.998 --> 19:30.168
[both growling]

19:30.252 --> 19:31.461
[screaming]

19:31.545 --> 19:33.922
Huh, thanks a lot,
Captain Wimpbeard.

19:34.006 --> 19:36.425
Ahh!

19:36.508 --> 19:38.176
Hey, guys.
Great to see you.

19:38.260 --> 19:42.806
Just wish it wasn't while
being thrown to our doom.

19:42.890 --> 19:44.308
If we don't make it,

19:44.391 --> 19:46.810
I just want to say
I love you guys.

19:46.894 --> 19:48.562
I love you guys
so much.

19:48.645 --> 19:50.063
[crying]

19:50.147 --> 19:52.941
- Me too.
- If only Pig were here.

19:53.025 --> 19:54.943
Then we could all
burn together.

19:55.027 --> 20:00.240
[all sobbing]

20:00.324 --> 20:03.994
[all screaming]

20:04.077 --> 20:05.579
{\an1}Hey, Goat.
If you melt before me,

20:05.662 --> 20:06.872
{\an1}can I have your
smartphone?

20:06.955 --> 20:08.832
But you're gonna melt
right after me.

20:08.916 --> 20:10.751
Can I have it anyway?

20:10.834 --> 20:13.003
[all screaming]

20:13.086 --> 20:16.965
Oh, oh, yeah, my official
Fudge-pocalypse umbrella.

20:17.049 --> 20:19.009
Hold on tight, guys.

20:19.092 --> 20:21.011
[all screaming]

20:21.094 --> 20:23.889
[all grunting]

20:23.972 --> 20:25.807
Sweet mama's monkeys!

20:25.891 --> 20:27.059
We're alive!

20:27.142 --> 20:29.436
Hey, what's that?

20:29.519 --> 20:31.355
You see?
I was right!

20:31.438 --> 20:35.817
There is treasure here.

20:35.901 --> 20:39.863
- [screaming]
- Hello.

20:39.947 --> 20:42.324
[all cheering]

20:42.407 --> 20:44.076
{\an1}Pig's okay.
Ew.

20:44.159 --> 20:46.662
{\an1}He's horrifyingly naked,
but he's okay.

20:46.745 --> 20:50.499
We had the treasure
under our clothes all along.

20:50.582 --> 20:53.168
The treasure of nudity.

20:53.251 --> 20:54.544
{\an1}Does this chest
get Wi-Fi?

20:54.628 --> 20:58.674
{\an1}Of course.
The password is "Pickle Milk."

20:58.757 --> 20:59.675
[gagging]

20:59.758 --> 21:05.806
[all screaming]

21:10.769 --> 21:11.728
[camera snaps]

21:11.812 --> 21:14.773
[tropical music]

21:14.856 --> 21:17.192
♪ ♪

21:17.275 --> 21:19.152
{\an3}Hmm?
[gasps]

21:19.236 --> 21:21.405
[chittering]

21:21.488 --> 21:25.450
{\an3}Goat, you look like
you were holding in a fart.

21:25.534 --> 21:27.202
I was.
[squeaking]

21:27.285 --> 21:29.329
And now I'm not.

21:29.413 --> 21:31.915
{\an1}Hey, Cricket,
sorry I ruined your lab

21:31.999 --> 21:33.583
{\an1}and cause
The Fudge-pocalypse.

21:33.667 --> 21:35.043
No, it's my fault.

21:35.127 --> 21:37.796
{\an3}I built the machine
that caused all the problems.

21:37.879 --> 21:40.215
{\an1}Oh, yeah, You're right.
It was your fault.

21:40.298 --> 21:41.299
But--phew.

21:41.383 --> 21:44.136
{\an1}[gasps]
Our treehouse!

21:44.219 --> 21:47.055
[all cheering]

21:47.139 --> 21:50.559
[chittering]

21:50.642 --> 21:52.853
(Banana)
Does this bubble get Wi-Fi?

21:52.936 --> 21:54.479
[all screaming]

21:54.563 --> 21:55.939
(all)
Pig Goat Banana Cricket

21:56.023 --> 21:58.775
Fudge-pocalypse Survival
High Five!

21:58.859 --> 22:00.444
The end.

22:01.778 --> 22:04.740
{\an8}[slow guitar music]

22:04.823 --> 22:12.831
{\an8}♪ ♪

22:25.010 --> 22:27.971
{\an8}[squeaking]
